The postabdomen is long and terminates posteriorly with two postabdominal claws. A single row of anal spines runs ventro-laterally on each side of the postabdomen (range 
13–17
). There is one basal spine on each postabdominal claw, and each claw invariably has a row of denticles running laterally from the base of the claw to its midpoint.

